# DS Component from Figma

Use this rule when building a new Design System component from a Figma spec.

## Project structure

```
packages/
  design-tokens/          → @ds-12/design-tokens
    src/
      tokens.generated.css  ← Style Dictionary output, do NOT edit
      tokens.web.css        ← web-specific layer, exported as tokens.css
      tokens.theme.css      ← generated @theme inline bridge for Tailwind v4
    scripts/
      generate-theme.mjs    ← regenerates tokens.theme.css
  ui/                     → @ds-12/ui
    src/
      tailwind.css          ← Tailwind v4 entry (tokens + theme bridge)
      components/           ← DS components (lowercase folder names)
      lib/
        utils.ts            ← cn() helper (clsx + tailwind-merge)
  utils/                  → @ds-12/utils
apps/
  storybook/              ← component stories + Vite aliases for local dev
```

## Package names & imports

| Package | Import examples |
|---|---|
| `@ds-12/design-tokens` | `@ds-12/design-tokens/tokens.css`, `@ds-12/design-tokens/theme.css` |
| `@ds-12/ui` | `@ds-12/ui/button`, `@ds-12/ui/tailwind.css`, `@ds-12/ui/style.css` |

Apps using `@ds-12/ui` must configure Tailwind v4 and import `@ds-12/ui/tailwind.css` in global CSS. Storybook does this in `.storybook/styles.css` with `@tailwindcss/vite` in `.storybook/main.ts`.

Components side-effect-import their own CSS only (tokens arrive via the app-level Tailwind entry):

```ts
import "./button.css";
```

## Step 1 — Setup tokens.web.css

Update `packages/design-tokens/src/tokens.web.css` (create if missing):

```css
@import "./tokens.generated.css";

:root {
  /* --- Web platform extensions --- */
  /* Focus ring, cursor, border-style, transition */

  /* --- Component tokens: [component] --- */
  /* Map to tokens.generated.css; add TODOs for unmapped Figma values */
}
```

Rules:
- Only add web-specific tokens or tokens missing from `tokens.generated.css`
- Do NOT duplicate or override values already in `tokens.generated.css`
- Prefer aliasing generated/semantic tokens: `--badge-radius: var(--radius-xsmall);`
- If a design token is wrong or missing, add a TODO and flag it as a Design System issue — do not silently fix it here

```css
/* TODO: needs token — current value: 20px */
```

### Token resolution (colors)

Resolve color values in this order:

1. **Repo tokens** — search `packages/design-tokens/src/tokens.generated.css` and `tokens.web.css` for a matching `--token-name`.
2. **Figma Variables** — if no repo token matches (or the generated name differs), call Figma MCP `get_variable_defs` with the component `fileKey` and `nodeId`. Variables return canonical names and resolved values, e.g. `color/semantic/canvas-moderate` → `#f7f8f8`.
3. **Map variable → CSS custom property** — convert the Figma path to the repo naming convention: slash segments become hyphens, prefixed with `--`.

   | Figma variable | Repo CSS custom property |
   |---|---|
   | `color/semantic/canvas-moderate` | `--color-semantic-canvas-moderate` |
   | `color/semantic/text-brand-bold` | `--color-semantic-text-brand-bold` |
   | `color/semantic/border-information-bold` | `--color-semantic-border-information-bold` |

4. **Re-check repo tokens** — after mapping, grep `tokens.generated.css` again for that `--color-*` name. If it exists, use `var(--color-semantic-…)`.
5. **Alias in `tokens.web.css`** — if the Figma variable resolves to a value that only exists under a different generated token (e.g. Figma `border-information-bold` → repo `--color-blue-500`), alias the component token to the generated one and leave a TODO noting the naming gap.
6. **Last resort** — if the variable is not in Figma and not in repo tokens, add a TODO with the Figma variable path and resolved hex/rgba value. Do not hardcode colors in component CSS.

For non-color tokens (spacing, radius, typography), prefer repo tokens first; use `get_variable_defs` only when the Figma spec references a variable name that does not appear in `tokens.generated.css`.

## Step 2 — Fetch component from Figma

Use Figma MCP (`get_design_context`) to fetch the target component by node ID.

Extract:
- Variants and visual differences between them
- Spacing, sizing, typography values
- Border, radius, shadow, color per variant and state (hover, focus, disabled)

Cross-reference each raw value against `tokens.generated.css` (see **Token resolution** above for colors):
- Match found → use `var(--token-name)`
- Color with no repo match → `get_variable_defs` → map to `--color-*` → alias in `tokens.web.css` or TODO
- No match after both sources → TODO comment with Figma variable path and resolved value in `tokens.web.css`

## Step 3 — Build the component

Create files under `packages/ui/src/components/[name]/` (lowercase, e.g. `button`, `badge`):

```
[name]/
  index.tsx
  [name].css          ← scoped styles (required for visual components)
```

### Stack

- **Base UI** (`@base-ui/react`) — interactive primitives (e.g. `Button`, `useRender`)
- **CVA** (`class-variance-authority`) — variant class names
- **Scoped CSS** — `ds-[name]` / `ds-[name]--[variant]` classes backed by CSS custom properties
- **Design tokens** — all visual values via `var(--token)` from `@ds-12/design-tokens/tokens.css`
- **`cn()`** — from `../../lib/utils.ts` when merging optional `className` props

Do **not** use Tailwind utility classes for component styling. The repo uses token-driven scoped CSS in components. Tailwind v4 is for app-level layout and Storybook wrappers only.

After editing `tokens.generated.css` or `tokens.web.css`, regenerate the Tailwind bridge:

```bash
vp run @ds-12/design-tokens#generate:theme
```

### Naming conventions

| Layer | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Folder | lowercase | `packages/ui/src/components/badge/` |
| CSS block | `ds-[name]` | `.ds-badge` |
| CSS modifier | `ds-[name]--[variant]` | `.ds-badge--bold` |
| CSS element | `ds-[name]__[part]` | `.ds-badge__icon` |
| CVA base class | `ds-[name]` | `cva("ds-badge", …)` |

### Component token pattern

Define component tokens in `tokens.web.css`:

```css
/* --- Component tokens: badge --- */
--badge-radius: var(--radius-xsmall);
--badge-sm-gap: var(--spacing-xxsmall);
/* TODO: needs token — current value: 20px */
--badge-lg-icon-size: 20px;
```

Use them in `[name].css`. For variant-specific values, set local custom properties on modifier classes:

```css
.ds-badge--subtle.ds-badge--neutral {
  --badge-fill: var(--badge-neutral-subtle-fill);
  --badge-label-fill: var(--badge-neutral-subtle-label-fill);
}

.ds-badge {
  background-color: var(--badge-fill);
  color: var(--badge-label-fill);
}
```

### CVA pattern

Map variants to scoped CSS classes (not Tailwind strings):

```ts
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";

const buttonVariants = cva("ds-button", {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      primary: "ds-button--primary",
      secondary: "ds-button--secondary",
    },
    size: {
      sm: "ds-button--sm",
      md: "ds-button--md",
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: {
    variant: "primary",
    size: "md",
  },
});
```

### Icons

Use the shared `Icon` component with `@material-symbols/font-400`:

```tsx
import { Icon } from "../icon/index.tsx";

<Icon name="check_circle" variant="filled" />
```

`Icon` reads size from `BadgeIconSizeContext` when nested inside `Badge`.

### Rules

- No hardcoded visual values — use a token or leave a TODO comment
- Variants and states must map to the Figma spec
- Do not add visual opinions outside of what Figma specifies
- Export the component from `packages/ui/src/index.ts`

## Step 4 — Storybook

Add `apps/storybook/src/stories/[name]/[name].stories.tsx`:

```ts
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from "@storybook/react-vite";
import { Button } from "@ds-12/ui/button";
```

Storybook resolves `@ds-12/ui/*` imports via the `@ds-12/ui` alias in `apps/storybook/vite.config.ts` (maps to `packages/ui/src/components`).

Add a subpath export in `packages/ui/package.json`:

```json
"./button": "./src/components/button/index.tsx"
```

Follow existing story patterns: `tags: ["autodocs"]`, variant/size controls, `AllVariants` showcase story.

## Step 5 — Validate

```bash
cd packages/ui && vp check
cd apps/storybook && npm run build-storybook
```

## Output checklist

- [ ] `packages/design-tokens/src/tokens.web.css` updated with component token aliases
- [ ] `packages/ui/src/components/[name]/index.tsx` created
- [ ] `packages/ui/src/components/[name]/[name].css` created with `ds-[name]` classes
- [ ] `packages/ui/src/index.ts` exports the component and types
- [ ] `packages/ui/package.json` has a `./[name]` subpath export
- [ ] `apps/storybook/vite.config.ts` alias added
- [ ] `apps/storybook/src/stories/[name]/[name].stories.tsx` created
- [ ] Color tokens resolved via repo tokens or Figma Variables (`get_variable_defs`) before falling back to TODOs
- [ ] All unmapped values have `/* TODO: needs token — current value: … */` comments (include Figma variable path when known)
- [ ] List of TODOs that require Design System decisions (token missing, token wrong, design ambiguous, Figma/repo naming mismatch)
